WEBVTT

1
00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:16.640
- Mom. I want a balloon.
- No. no.

2
00:00:16.720 --> 00:00:19.200
- Please. Mom.
- It's Navya's birthday in two days.

3
00:00:19.280 --> 00:00:20.600
we'll get it then. Okay?

4
00:00:20.680 --> 00:00:22.280
- Okay. Promise?
- Yes. promise.

5
00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:23.320
Tomatoes for sale!

6
00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:26.120
- Hey. stop.
- Take some. madam. The tomatoes are good.

7
00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:29.320
- How much?
- Seventy rupees a kilo. madam.

8
00:00:29.400 --> 00:00:31.080
- What?
- Seventy rupees a kilo.

9
00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:32.320
Are they made of gold?

10
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:34.000
- Madam. take some.
- Not at all.

11
00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:36.480
- I'll give you a discount. Madam!
- No. leave it.

12
00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:39.880
How much for the tomatoes?

13
00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:42.360
- Fifty rupees a kilo. madam.
- And onions and potatoes?

14
00:00:42.440 --> 00:00:45.480
Onion is 60 rupees a kilo
and potato is 55 rupees a kilo.

15
00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:48.440
Don't fleece me by calling me madam.
Tell a fair price.

16
00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:50.840
Madam. I'm giving you the best price.

17
00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.240
- Why would I fleece you?
- Okay.

18
00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:57.120
A kilo of onions. two kilo potatoes
and a kilo of tomatoes.

19
00:00:57.200 --> 00:00:58.720
- Okay. please pick the tomatoes.
- Yes.

20
00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:01.680
Baby. see? Red tomatoes. Only red. Okay?

21
00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:03.480
Come on. put the red ones in this.

22
00:01:11.560 --> 00:01:13.280
- Here you go.
- Your payment.

23
00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:21.480
This is not four kilos.

24
00:01:23.520 --> 00:01:26.160
No way. madam?
I just weighed it in front of you.

25
00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:29.640
Give it to me. I will weigh it again.

26
00:01:37.760 --> 00:01:39.240
See for yourself.

27
00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:48.800
Listen. I can tell you that it's not
more than 3.5 kilos as I held the bags.

28
00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:54.440
Either you tell me the truth
or face the consequences.

29
00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:58.080
Shall I weigh it elsewhere?

30
00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:06.440
I tipped the scale by ten percent.
It was my mistake. I'm sorry.

31
00:02:06.520 --> 00:02:09.280
Replace the scales right now
and weigh it properly.

32
00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:10.200
Okay.

33
00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:17.360
- Good evening. sir.
- Good evening. Kamath.

34
00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:19.480
The new AC has revoked your suspension.

35
00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:21.760
<i>Come to the office immediately.</i>

36
00:02:22.880 --> 00:02:24.040
Sir.

37
00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:39.000
<i>This is my department's
human weighing scale. Mitali Kamath.</i>

38
00:02:43.960 --> 00:02:45.120
Harder. Come on.

39
00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:49.360
<i>She's also known
as the Google of our department.</i>

40
00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:51.600
<i>Customs officers are clueless</i>

41
00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:55.360
<i>about the value
of a lot of things in the world.</i>

42
00:02:55.440 --> 00:03:00.400
<i>But Mitali keeps track of the existence
of such exotic things and their value.</i>

43
00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:03.520
<i>This is her gift. and her passion too.</i>

44
00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:07.800
<i>She's a divorcee.
And she dotes on her daughter.</i>

45
00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:31.640
Kulveer Dhuria.

46
00:04:32.680 --> 00:04:34.760
Where from? Chhattisgarh?

47
00:04:41.200 --> 00:04:43.000
How long have you been working here?

48
00:04:43.600 --> 00:04:45.760
- Who are you. man. huh?
- Santa Claus.

49
00:04:46.960 --> 00:04:49.120
I've brought a gift for you.
just like Santa Claus.

50
00:04:55.880 --> 00:04:59.360
Don't waste your time
on those hippie foreigners.

51
00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:03.320
Let them go. you won't find a thing.
They are backpackers.

52
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:08.280
This couple is also not hiding anything.

53
00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:11.760
They are bringing
some dead relative's ashes.

54
00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:20.560
Look straight ahead.

55
00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:23.080
Go and check that guy in the blue jacket.

56
00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:25.560
He surely has something to declare.

57
00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:30.280
But why are you telling me all this?

58
00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:33.600
Because your face shows
that you haven't caught anyone to date.

59
00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:44.520
Excuse me. sir. Hi.

60
00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:45.920
Where are you coming from?

61
00:05:46.880 --> 00:05:48.440
- Bangkok.
- Bangkok?

62
00:05:48.520 --> 00:05:50.520
- Your passport. please.
- Sure.

63
00:05:56.280 --> 00:05:57.640
Thank you.

64
00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:04.600
Hey! What the hell is that?

65
00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:08.760
- Sir. these are marmosets.
- What?

66
00:06:08.840 --> 00:06:11.080
- Marmosets.
- Where did you get them from?

67
00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.360
- Got them from Thailand. but--
- From Thailand?

68
00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:16.840
Do you know they are illegal here?

69
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:20.240
Turn off your cameras. guys.
Turn off your cameras.

70
00:06:20.320 --> 00:06:22.480
- Do you have permission for these?
- No. sir.

71
00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:24.280
Then how could you bring them in?

72
00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:26.160
Sir. they're pets for kids...

73
00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:28.120
Kids liked them.
so you brought them along?

74
00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:29.680
Didn't you check our rules?

75
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:31.800
<i>These are pygmy marmoset monkeys.</i>

76
00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:34.240
<i>It's illegal
to bring them into our country.</i>

77
00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:37.760
<i>But they are a trend among the rich kids.</i>

78
00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:13.200
<i>This guy bought
two of these small monkeys at Bangkok.</i>

79
00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:18.200
<i>sedated them and put them in his
jacket pocket and brought them to India.</i>

80
00:07:22.360 --> 00:07:24.680
<i>The flight was delayed by a few hours.</i>

81
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:27.400
<i>and the monkeys' sedation wore off.</i>

82
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:30.720
<i>And as soon as they came to their senses.</i>

83
00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:34.760
<i>these little ones
started behaving like monkeys.</i>

84
00:07:34.840 --> 00:07:38.880
<i>How did Santa Claus get to know that this
guy was carrying monkeys in his pocket?</i>

85
00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:40.280
<i>God only knows.</i>

86
00:07:43.560 --> 00:07:48.640
<i>This guy calls himself Santa Claus.
actually his real name is Ravinder Gujjar.</i>

87
00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:51.360
<i>Gujjar is my best friend and batchmate.</i>

88
00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:55.440
Grandpa!

89
00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:03.320
<i>Gujjar's father. two of his brothers.
his sister and mother.</i>

90
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:07.360
<i>his paternal uncle and his wife.
his dad's sister and her husband</i>

91
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:10.760
<i>are employed in the Central Excise
or Income Tax department.</i>

92
00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:35.720
<i>If there was a competition
for the most corrupt family in India.</i>

93
00:08:35.800 --> 00:08:38.799
<i>Ravinder Gujjar's family
would've always won.</i>

94
00:08:45.159 --> 00:08:46.880
Come on. food is served. Come on.

95
00:09:02.560 --> 00:09:05.360
<i>Gujjar sort of hated this system
as he had grown up hearing their tales</i>

96
00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:07.280
<i>of corruption since childhood.</i>

97
00:09:11.560 --> 00:09:16.280
<i>So. on the first day he joined Customs.
he had vowed</i>

98
00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:19.040
<i>not to accept bribe. not even a penny.</i>

99
00:09:19.120 --> 00:09:20.960
<i>He hasn't broken that vow to date.</i>

100
00:09:24.680 --> 00:09:26.960
<i>He is hardly respected in the family.</i>

101
00:09:27.520 --> 00:09:29.640
<i>And everybody considers him to be crazy.</i>

102
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:33.040
<i>But Gujjar is not at all crazy.</i>

103
00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:36.320
<i>He is a soft-hearted romantic guy.</i>

104
00:09:36.840 --> 00:09:39.160
<i>Gujjar's love story is unique too.</i>

105
00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:41.120
<i>He had been working for just 15 days</i>

106
00:09:41.200 --> 00:09:44.920
<i>and he fell in love with the nice.</i>

107
00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:47.920
<i>homely-looking Meenakshi.
who worked at the duty-free shop.</i>

108
00:09:48.960 --> 00:09:51.480
<i>And Meenakshi liked Gujjar a lot too.</i>

109
00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:06.440
<i>They got into a routine
and two years passed by.</i>

110
00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:09.160
<i>Gujjar got into AIU.</i>

111
00:10:09.240 --> 00:10:12.240
<i>Gujjar and Meenakshi
took breaks at the same time.</i>

112
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:14.760
<i>and had tea from the runway canteen.</i>

113
00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:19.400
<i>At that time. Meenakshi wasn't aware</i>

114
00:10:19.480 --> 00:10:22.680
<i>that Gujjar used
to take her for tea outside</i>

115
00:10:22.760 --> 00:10:25.240
<i>because tea
was very expensive at the airport.</i>

116
00:10:27.560 --> 00:10:30.440
<i>Meenakshi's parents also loved Gujjar.</i>

117
00:10:30.520 --> 00:10:33.400
<i>As he made no mention of dowry</i>

118
00:10:33.480 --> 00:10:35.720
<i>and said that he'd do a court marriage.</i>

119
00:10:39.320 --> 00:10:42.320
Everything is finalized.
You guys just have to sign.

120
00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:45.680
I'll submit this. dates will be announced.
Then you'll get married in a jiffy.

121
00:10:45.760 --> 00:10:47.960
Thank you. Done. I'll be back.

122
00:10:51.200 --> 00:10:53.040
<i>It happened just last month.</i>

123
00:10:53.120 --> 00:10:58.080
<i>We were waiting for Meenakshi
and her family at the court...</i>

124
00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:20.720
<i>...but she did not come.</i>

125
00:11:20.800 --> 00:11:23.200
<i>Don't worry. No one died.</i>

126
00:11:23.280 --> 00:11:27.080
<i>It so happened
that the day Meenakshi realized</i>

127
00:11:27.160 --> 00:11:29.640
<i>that Gujjar was not trying to impress her</i>

128
00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:31.760
<i>with his honesty.</i>

129
00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:35.640
<i>He actually just wanted
to survive on his salary alone.</i>

130
00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:39.040
<i>That day marked
the end of Gujjar's love story.</i>

131
00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:51.120
Ravinder. your exile is over.

132
00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:55.720
Had I known that you were coming back too.
I'd have done a couple of more gigs.

133
00:12:55.800 --> 00:13:00.240
Good one.
Your sense of humor is still intact. Good.

134
00:13:31.200 --> 00:13:34.080
Fifty lakhs in here.
I found it under the washroom shelf.

135
00:13:34.920 --> 00:13:36.040
Put it in the seizure.

136
00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:40.680
Everything about you
looks very dicey to me.

137
00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:44.200
Is it just me
or have you called others too?

138
00:13:45.080 --> 00:13:46.440
Mitali and Ravinder.

139
00:13:47.240 --> 00:13:49.200
How will it happen without the trinity?

140
00:13:59.880 --> 00:14:03.000
Hey. Meena! Your suspension's over?

141
00:14:03.080 --> 00:14:04.840
I don't know. man. Let's see.

142
00:14:19.960 --> 00:14:22.480
Excuse me. Sir is ready for you.

143
00:14:34.720 --> 00:14:38.200
Let me have a chat with him
and then we can...

144
00:14:38.280 --> 00:14:39.280
Sir.

145
00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:41.880
Right. Carry on. Call me in the evening.

146
00:14:43.480 --> 00:14:45.840
- Hello.
- Arjun Meena reporting for duty. sir.

147
00:14:45.920 --> 00:14:47.280
I've heard a lot about you.

148
00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:50.320
- The most amazing things of course.
- Thank you. sir.

149
00:14:50.400 --> 00:14:52.160
By the way. we've also been told

150
00:14:52.240 --> 00:14:55.640
that a very young and dynamic officer
has joined the department.

151
00:14:56.840 --> 00:14:58.960
This is Mitali Kamath and Ravinder Gujjar.

152
00:14:59.040 --> 00:15:00.800
- Hello. sir.
- Hello. Mitali.

153
00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:02.520
- Hi.
- Hi. sir.

154
00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:04.760
My name is Prakash Kumar.

155
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:07.840
And I've been given the mandate
to end smuggling at this airport.

156
00:15:07.920 --> 00:15:10.360
But I cannot do that without you three.

157
00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:13.320
When I was chosen for this job.
I asked around

158
00:15:13.400 --> 00:15:15.720
and got to know about you three.

159
00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:19.880
And I was also told
the reason you guys were suspended.

160
00:15:22.040 --> 00:15:23.160
But welcome back.

161
00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:26.640
So long as I am here.
you needn't worry about anything.

162
00:15:27.280 --> 00:15:28.600
Catch whoever you want.

163
00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:33.200
But we've to ensure that smugglers forget
the Mumbai International Airport route.

164
00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:36.320
Do your duty without any tension.

165
00:15:36.400 --> 00:15:38.280
As long as you all
are playing by the book.

166
00:15:38.360 --> 00:15:41.280
I will be responsible
for anything that happens to you.

167
00:15:41.360 --> 00:15:42.520
- Understood?
- Sir.

168
00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:43.840
- Sir.
- Yes. sir.

169
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:46.160
Our mission is
to destroy the Choudhary Syndicate.

170
00:15:46.240 --> 00:15:49.240
which brings
the maximum contraband to Mumbai.

171
00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:51.440
Based on intelligence from various sources

172
00:15:51.520 --> 00:15:52.960
I have compiled a report

173
00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:55.440
on the main players
of Choudhary Syndicate.

174
00:15:55.520 --> 00:15:57.080
I want you all to have a look at it.

175
00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:03.000
Choudhary Syndicate operates from London.
Italy. Middle East. Ethiopia and Bangkok.

176
00:16:03.840 --> 00:16:07.360
The leader of
this entire Syndicate is Bada Choudhary.

177
00:16:07.440 --> 00:16:09.840
who uses his brain to run

178
00:16:09.920 --> 00:16:13.200
this entire syndicate
from Milan through his couriers.

179
00:16:13.280 --> 00:16:15.200
<i>Choudhary's back story
is quite interesting too.</i>

180
00:16:15.280 --> 00:16:18.040
{\an8}<i>It's a story of twin brothers.</i>

181
00:16:18.120 --> 00:16:20.680
{\an8}<i>Bada Choudhary and Chota Choudhary.</i>

182
00:16:20.760 --> 00:16:23.760
<i>Just as Vijay worked as a laborer
in</i> Deewaar <i>so Ravi could go to school.</i>

183
00:16:23.840 --> 00:16:27.960
<i>Similarly. Chota Choudhary ran
an illicit trade so as to educate Bada.</i>

184
00:16:28.040 --> 00:16:28.920
Betrayal?

185
00:16:31.880 --> 00:16:34.640
<i>Bada Choudhary worked hard in the hope</i>

186
00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:37.440
<i>that he'd study hard
and make the younger one quit his ways.</i>

187
00:16:38.360 --> 00:16:40.880
<i>But here. Chota's clout was growing.</i>

188
00:16:40.960 --> 00:16:44.280
<i>And big gangs
were reaching out to hook up with him.</i>

189
00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:49.600
<i>But he loved his freedom.</i>

190
00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:50.840
Join us.

191
00:16:50.920 --> 00:16:52.240
<i>And he didn't want to give it up.</i>

192
00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:53.160
{\an8}NO

193
00:16:53.920 --> 00:16:55.760
<i>But the story took a turn the day</i>

194
00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:57.840
- Yes.
<i>- Bada Choudhary became an engineer.</i>

195
00:17:00.160 --> 00:17:02.560
Pick it up. Hello?

196
00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:07.440
He's become an engineer.
My brother is an engineer.

197
00:17:07.520 --> 00:17:11.280
<i>Chota Choudhary was very happy.
And he was on his way home when...</i>

198
00:17:29.520 --> 00:17:33.160
<i>That day Bada burnt all his degrees
in his brother's pyre.</i>

199
00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:37.200
<i>And he decided what
he wanted to do with his life.</i>

200
00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:42.640
<i>With Sharma</i> ji'<i>s help. he first</i>

201
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:45.160
<i>killed all those who had murdered Chota.</i>

202
00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:07.760
<i>And then. on Sharma</i> ji'<i>s advice.
he smuggled his first consignment.</i>

203
00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:09.120
<i>Back in 2003.</i>

204
00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:12.320
<i>mobile phones
were rapidly gaining ground in India.</i>

205
00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:15.080
<i>Thousands were smuggling mobile phones.</i>

206
00:18:15.160 --> 00:18:18.640
<i>But Bada Choudhary came up
with an idea to smuggle something unique.</i>

207
00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:19.840
<i>Memory cards.</i>

208
00:18:19.920 --> 00:18:23.200
<i>Smaller than two-inches.
thousands of memory cards</i>

209
00:18:23.280 --> 00:18:25.560
<i>could easily fit into a small box.</i>

210
00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:28.680
<i>Choudhary made 1.5 lakhs
with his very first consignment.</i>

211
00:18:28.760 --> 00:18:30.720
<i>Choudhary had found his niche.</i>

212
00:18:30.800 --> 00:18:32.640
<i>And that was smuggling.</i>

213
00:18:33.440 --> 00:18:37.080
<i>And he started bringing everything
from abroad that had a margin to Mumbai.</i>

214
00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:41.000
<i>As he was passing
through airports regularly. he understood</i>

215
00:18:41.080 --> 00:18:43.120
<i>that some customs officers
could be bribed.</i>

216
00:18:44.360 --> 00:18:47.000
<i>So he made deals with all of them.</i>

217
00:18:47.080 --> 00:18:49.040
<i>An organized payment structure was set up.</i>

218
00:18:49.120 --> 00:18:52.400
<i>And he began running his shady business
with complete integrity.</i>

219
00:18:52.480 --> 00:18:55.840
<i>His business kept growing.
and he needed more people.</i>

220
00:18:55.920 --> 00:18:59.320
This is Anna.
his nephew Rahul. and this is Suresh.

221
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.560
They smuggle gold
from the Middle East into India.

222
00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:05.840
<i>Meetings with Anna
helped him understand the gold business.</i>

223
00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:08.360
<i>Anna became his top officer in Al Dirah.</i>

224
00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:10.840
And this is Carlos Junior.

225
00:19:10.920 --> 00:19:13.200
{\an8}He sends drugs
from Ethiopia into our country.

226
00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:16.720
{\an8}<i>The responsibility
of collection and sale of stuff</i>

227
00:19:16.800 --> 00:19:19.080
{\an8}<i>brought by the couriers
rests with Ramesh bhai.</i>

228
00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:23.480
This is Mrs. Syed. who handles
the operations in London and Italy.

229
00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:26.680
<i>She sends high-end bags
and luxury goods to India from there.</i>

230
00:19:26.760 --> 00:19:29.160
<i>Been in business for 20 years.</i>

231
00:19:29.240 --> 00:19:32.960
<i>Bada Choudhary's Syndicate
is India's biggest smuggling syndicate.</i>

232
00:19:34.800 --> 00:19:36.800
<i>At a photo shoot
for a fashion show in Milan.</i>

233
00:19:37.440 --> 00:19:39.560
<i>Choudhary's eyes fell on a swimwear model.</i>

234
00:19:39.640 --> 00:19:42.840
<i>He fell for her and that model converted.</i>

235
00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:48.160
<i>Bianca became a true Indian
and she got a new name. Binita Choudhary.</i>

236
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:52.440
<i>They have a four-year-old son now.</i>

237
00:19:52.520 --> 00:19:56.080
<i>And the happy family
lives comfortably in a villa on Lake Como.</i>

238
00:20:00.760 --> 00:20:03.640
Now. what I am going to tell you
stays inside this room.

239
00:20:04.560 --> 00:20:07.440
The three of you will work
for Central Intelligence Unit from today.

240
00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:09.360
Arjun. you will lead this op.

241
00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:12.360
To the outside world.
you are still the same.

242
00:20:12.440 --> 00:20:14.800
You'll continue to do what you were doing.

243
00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:18.480
There is no other way
to flush out corruption from the system.

244
00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.160
From today. our only goal will be

245
00:20:21.240 --> 00:20:24.440
to eliminate the Choudhary Syndicate.

246
00:20:24.520 --> 00:20:28.800
Find smugglers. find corrupt officers
and let's do a thorough clean up.

247
00:20:29.880 --> 00:20:31.240
- Clear?
- Right. sir.

248
00:20:31.320 --> 00:20:34.720
Sir. we will need more people.

249
00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:35.960
Send me a list.

250
00:20:36.040 --> 00:20:37.760
Sir. may I ask a question?

251
00:20:40.280 --> 00:20:42.560
Hope you won't be transferred soon?

252
00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:47.880
No. I mean you brought us here and then--

253
00:20:47.960 --> 00:20:49.440
I'm here till the election results.

254
00:20:50.760 --> 00:20:51.880
I don't know after that.

255
00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:54.320
Good to know. sir.

256
00:20:55.720 --> 00:20:58.280
You just don't think. do you?
You just say what you want.

257
00:20:58.360 --> 00:21:01.320
Hey. what did I say? We need to know.

258
00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:03.720
He has put us on the hook.
hope he will stick with us.

259
00:21:03.800 --> 00:21:05.000
- It's simple. man.
- Just a sec.

260
00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:11.240
Hello.

261
00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:18.040
Don't create a scene here. I can explain.

262
00:21:18.120 --> 00:21:20.120
No. there's no need for that.

263
00:21:20.920 --> 00:21:22.680
I just came to give you this.

264
00:21:23.800 --> 00:21:25.440
That'll be 450 rupees.

265
00:21:25.520 --> 00:21:28.640
Two hundred for the sweets
and 250 for the garland.

266
00:21:30.600 --> 00:21:33.440
You've come to ask me for money?

267
00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:36.520
Yes. why? That was my hard-earned money.

268
00:21:37.080 --> 00:21:39.360
I was going to spend it on our wedding.

269
00:21:39.440 --> 00:21:41.600
You don't want to marry me.
return my money.

270
00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:43.400
Hand it over.

271
00:21:49.640 --> 00:21:51.280
Neha. give me 500 bucks.

272
00:21:51.360 --> 00:21:53.120
Give me 500 bucks.

273
00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:56.400
- What happened?
- Just give me.

274
00:22:04.440 --> 00:22:06.240
- Oh. man.
- Keep the change.

275
00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:11.080
Hey. madam. I'm not a waiter
that I'll keep the change.

276
00:22:11.160 --> 00:22:12.760
I am a Customs Officer. Do you get it?

277
00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:15.960
"Keep the change."

278
00:22:16.040 --> 00:22:18.320
Meena. come here.

279
00:22:18.960 --> 00:22:20.960
Hey. come here. bro.

280
00:22:24.320 --> 00:22:25.880
Give her 50 bucks.

281
00:22:28.360 --> 00:22:30.480
- Gujjar...
- I need to pay her. bro. Come on.

282
00:22:35.640 --> 00:22:39.000
Wait a sec. She owes you gas money too.

283
00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:43.680
Fifty bucks for the gas.

284
00:22:46.800 --> 00:22:47.680
I'm so sorry.

285
00:23:32.760 --> 00:23:34.600
- Good morning. sir.
- Good morning.

286
00:23:48.480 --> 00:23:50.600
- Good morning. sir.
- Good morning.

287
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:51.760
He's sitting outside.

288
00:24:04.720 --> 00:24:06.520
- Won't you try the--
- No!

289
00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:09.480
- Good morning. Ranjeet.
- Good morning. Sharma <i>ji.</i>

290
00:24:09.560 --> 00:24:11.120
- Come on. baby. Let's go.
- Come.

291
00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:13.080
Go! Go and play.

292
00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:14.760
- Good morning.
- Please come.

293
00:24:19.760 --> 00:24:23.600
Ranjeet. how come seven officers
got transferred in Mumbai in one go?

294
00:24:24.240 --> 00:24:25.520
Whose fault was it?

295
00:24:25.600 --> 00:24:27.560
It was due to Pawar's foolishness.

296
00:24:29.200 --> 00:24:30.440
He messed with the wrong guy.

297
00:24:33.120 --> 00:24:35.840
- And who is replacing them?
- We will get to know by evening.

298
00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:39.840
Don't worry. It happens sometimes.

299
00:24:39.920 --> 00:24:41.880
I don't know.

300
00:24:51.360 --> 00:24:53.600
I was thinking of getting
Gautam Jha into the team.

301
00:24:54.480 --> 00:24:56.680
Gautam has no interest in Operations.

302
00:24:56.760 --> 00:24:58.800
He has joined the Rewards team.

303
00:24:58.880 --> 00:25:01.040
He says. he'll stay there till he retires.

304
00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:04.960
- Where is Sajjad nowadays?
- Where else?

305
00:25:05.040 --> 00:25:07.200
Like a moth is drawn to a flame.
he'll turn up.

306
00:25:07.280 --> 00:25:09.680
Guys. we better explain clearly to him

307
00:25:09.760 --> 00:25:14.080
not to blackmail movie stars passing
through the airport. He clings to them.

308
00:25:14.160 --> 00:25:16.560
- Let's call Vincent.
- Yeah.

309
00:25:17.840 --> 00:25:20.560
- Contact Shreelata too.
- Yes. Lucknow airport.

310
00:25:21.600 --> 00:25:24.080
Bro. let's call Shreelata.
Should we call Awasthi?

311
00:25:25.560 --> 00:25:28.920
<i>As instructed by Prakash sir.
we started putting our team together.</i>

312
00:25:32.320 --> 00:25:36.840
<i>We called officers like Shreelata Nayyar.
Vincent Joy. Sajjad Sheikh. K.P. Awasthi</i>

313
00:25:36.920 --> 00:25:40.720
<i>from different corners
of India urgently to Mumbai.</i>

314
00:25:41.840 --> 00:25:45.080
<i>All these officers
had one thing in common.</i>

315
00:25:45.160 --> 00:25:49.240
<i>All of them were honest.
intelligent and incorruptible.</i>

316
00:26:03.400 --> 00:26:05.120
- Good morning. sir.
- Good morning.

317
00:26:05.200 --> 00:26:06.520
- Sit down.
- Thank you. sir.

318
00:27:02.480 --> 00:27:06.600
<i>On our first day at work.
none of us had a clue</i>

319
00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:08.680
<i>that we'd have to pay such a big price</i>

320
00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:12.200
<i>for our honesty in the days to come.</i>

321
00:27:46.440 --> 00:27:47.440
Found anything?

322
00:27:56.440 --> 00:27:58.360
- What is it?
- Good morning. ma'am.

323
00:27:58.440 --> 00:28:00.680
Don't breathe down my neck. Move.

324
00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:04.360
Sorry. ma'am.
I was told to buddy up with you.

325
00:28:08.960 --> 00:28:13.280
What custom duty will you charge
a passenger who brings.

326
00:28:13.800 --> 00:28:15.800
and declares two cartons of cigarettes?

327
00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:17.800
Ma'am... Thirty. ma'am.

328
00:28:17.880 --> 00:28:19.160
Wrong answer.

329
00:28:19.880 --> 00:28:22.680
Awasthi. he needs to be trained.

330
00:28:23.960 --> 00:28:26.480
Come on. Sit down.

331
00:28:42.760 --> 00:28:44.560
- Stop this bag.
- Okay. ma'am.

332
00:28:45.360 --> 00:28:46.760
What's in there?

333
00:28:46.840 --> 00:28:50.240
Ma'am. there is shampoo. toiletries.

334
00:28:50.320 --> 00:28:52.360
chocolates. some toys.

335
00:28:52.440 --> 00:28:55.440
a mobile phone charger.
two watches and jewelry.

336
00:28:56.480 --> 00:28:58.360
But. ma'am. that's not gold. it's steel...

337
00:28:59.640 --> 00:29:01.320
Just a sec. ma'am.

338
00:29:03.320 --> 00:29:04.680
It's stainless steel. ma'am.

339
00:29:04.760 --> 00:29:06.480
- It's stainless steel?
- Yes. ma'am.

340
00:29:06.560 --> 00:29:09.320
- Shall we let it go?
- Yes. We can let it go.

341
00:29:11.280 --> 00:29:12.520
Come here.

342
00:29:14.080 --> 00:29:16.560
- Are these bags yours?
- Yeah.

343
00:29:17.200 --> 00:29:20.040
Grab your bags and come with me.
We need to check them.

344
00:29:20.680 --> 00:29:21.680
Sure.

345
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.440
- Help her.
- Yes. ma'am.

346
00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:34.920
Ma'am. what are these?

347
00:29:35.600 --> 00:29:37.720
These are toys for my niece.

348
00:29:37.800 --> 00:29:41.760
- Such big ones?
- Teddy bears are usually big.

349
00:29:42.960 --> 00:29:44.280
That's true.

350
00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:47.480
But you see ma'am. this one is Chanel.

351
00:29:48.040 --> 00:29:50.840
It's worth a little more than 50 lakhs.

352
00:29:50.920 --> 00:29:52.760
and the Black Sense Market is little less.

353
00:29:53.560 --> 00:29:55.400
They're limited edition Bearbricks.

354
00:29:55.480 --> 00:29:58.520
So. it's up to you now.
You wanna pay the duty

355
00:29:58.600 --> 00:30:01.880
or shall I confiscate these
and take you to court?

356
00:30:01.960 --> 00:30:02.920
Choice is yours.

357
00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:11.920
I'll pay the duty.

358
00:30:13.040 --> 00:30:14.800
- Jyoti.
- Yes. madam?

359
00:30:14.880 --> 00:30:16.000
Take her with you.

360
00:30:16.080 --> 00:30:17.680
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

361
00:30:24.640 --> 00:30:25.480
Ma'am?

362
00:30:26.480 --> 00:30:28.480
These toys look so ordinary.

363
00:30:28.560 --> 00:30:31.360
How did you know
that they're high value commodities?

364
00:30:31.960 --> 00:30:35.840
Because internet wasn't made just for
TikTok. Reels and Instagram.

365
00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:40.200
Do me a favor. Go left from here
and count all the washrooms and tell me.

366
00:30:40.280 --> 00:30:42.960
- Okay. ma'am.
- Hello? Put that back.

367
00:30:58.200 --> 00:31:00.560
- Yes. tell me.
- Will you come to the APIS room?

368
00:31:18.760 --> 00:31:21.640
- Yes. tell me.
- Arjun. look at this passenger.

369
00:31:21.720 --> 00:31:25.080
She's done 12 trips from Al Dirah
to Mumbai in the last six months.

370
00:31:25.160 --> 00:31:26.920
And in the last three years...

371
00:31:27.720 --> 00:31:31.240
London. Paris. Al Dirah...
She's been everywhere.

372
00:31:32.520 --> 00:31:36.120
So? She might be from a wealthy family.
What made you doubt her?

373
00:31:36.880 --> 00:31:41.600
Forget the girl.
Look at her flight details.

374
00:31:41.680 --> 00:31:44.760
London. Kolkata. Mumbai.
Paris. Delhi. Mumbai.

375
00:31:44.840 --> 00:31:46.280
Al Dirah. Pune. Mumbai.

376
00:31:46.360 --> 00:31:50.040
From international to domestic
and then from that domestic to Mumbai.

377
00:31:50.840 --> 00:31:54.200
But the domestic destination
is different every time.

378
00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:01.720
<i>Priya Khubchandani's travel history
was quite interesting.</i>

379
00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:05.840
<i>There's a small loophole
in airlines operations.</i>

380
00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:08.480
<i>Many planes are used
for international flights.</i>

381
00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:11.600
<i>And then. the same planes fly domestic.</i>

382
00:32:11.680 --> 00:32:15.840
<i>For example. Sitara's flight
comes from Al Dirah to Lucknow.</i>

383
00:32:15.920 --> 00:32:19.440
<i>The smuggler's courier boards
the international flight with the gold.</i>

384
00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:23.240
<i>And hides it in the toilet.</i>

385
00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:31.520
<i>After landing at Lucknow.
the courier confidently exits the plane.</i>

386
00:32:36.320 --> 00:32:38.760
<i>The passengers disembark
and plane is cleaned.</i>

387
00:32:40.720 --> 00:32:44.840
<i>The new crew will come.
then the plane will head towards Mumbai.</i>

388
00:32:44.920 --> 00:32:49.120
<i>and a courier gets on to the plane
and grabs the gold at the right moment.</i>

389
00:32:49.200 --> 00:32:54.000
<i>Seat belt signs are now off. However
keep your seatbelts loosely fastened.</i>

390
00:32:54.080 --> 00:32:56.480
<i>You may now use the washroom.</i>

391
00:32:59.240 --> 00:33:02.960
<i>And exits the Mumbai domestic airport
without any checking.</i>

392
00:33:03.040 --> 00:33:05.080
<i>There's no chance of getting caught.</i>

393
00:33:05.160 --> 00:33:08.160
<i>Because who the hell will
smuggle goods on a domestic flight?</i>

394
00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:11.360
I'll look into it.

395
00:33:24.520 --> 00:33:26.160
<i>Gujjar's shrewd eyes</i>

396
00:33:26.240 --> 00:33:30.400
<i>had caught this passenger.
Priya Khubchandani's travel pattern.</i>

397
00:33:37.160 --> 00:33:38.880
Excuse me. ma'am. Mumbai Customs.

398
00:33:39.480 --> 00:33:43.240
- Where are you coming from?
- Al Dirah. Any problem. Officer?

399
00:33:43.920 --> 00:33:47.080
- Do you have your boarding pass?
- Wait a sec.

400
00:33:52.200 --> 00:33:55.640
One of my officers has noticed
your MO and travel pattern.

401
00:37:58.840 --> 00:38:03.840
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
